				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Question on atk, ac, resist caps<a name="56076"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 11 04 11:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mmmm max cap is 250 atk, and the guide I just read was excellent and I just want to clarify something in one of the later posts. Max worn atk cap is 250 but self procs do count towards this cap, buffs cast on you from outside source do not. So Primal weapon proccing Avatar adding 100 to your atk will continue to add the full 100 until you wear over 150 worn atk, after this stage it will only take you from current worn atk value up to the 250 cap. 
<br />

<br />
Ferine Avatar cast by a Shaman or SoTP (Ranger) or Ferocity(Beastlord) will all add to your atk over the 250 worn cap and allow you to bufff your attack nice and high. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Tutuboy
<br />

<br />
PS, Dont forget Spirit of Billy and SK atk buffs to get this really maxed out, and worn regen cap is 35, FT is 15 (+4 from AA)</span></td>
